borrowSecondaryCurrencyToVault(address,u.notice: Allows a vault to borrow a secondary currency if it is whitelisted to do so

params.account: account that is borrowing the secondary currency
params.fCashToBorrow: fCash to borrow for the first and second secondary currencies
params.maxBorrowRate: maximum borrow rate for the first and second secondary currencies
params.minRollLendRate: max roll lend rate for the first and second borrow currencies

returns.underlyingTokensTransferred: amount of tokens transferred back to the vault

depositVaultCashToStrategyTokens(uint256.notice: Strategy vaults can call this method to deposit asset cash into strategy tokens.

params.assetCashInternal: the number of asset cash tokens to deposit (external)
params.maturity: the maturity of the vault where the redemption will take place
params.vaultData: arbitrary data to pass back to the vault for deposit

getCashRequiredToSettle(address,uint256).notice: View method to get the current amount of cash remaining to settle the vault

getVaultState(address,uint256).notice: View method to get vault state

initiateSecondaryBorrowSettlement(uint25.notice: MUST be called by vaults that are using secondary borrows to initiate the settlement process. Once settlement process has been initiated, no further secondary borrows may occur in this maturity. Repayments can only occur via the vault itself, individual accounts cannot repay secondary borrows after this occurs. Can only be called by the vault.

params.maturity: maturity in which to initiate settlement

returns.secondaryBorrowSnapshot: value of fCash in primary currency terms for both secondary borrow currencies

redeemStrategyTokensToCash(uint256,uint2.notice: Strategy vaults can call this method to redeem strategy tokens to cash and hold them as asset cash within the pool. This should typically be used during settlement but can also be used for vault-wide deleveraging.

params.maturity: the maturity of the vault where the redemption will take place
params.strategyTokensToRedeem: the number of strategy tokens redeemed
params.vaultData: arbitrary data to pass back to the vault

returns.assetCashRequiredToSettle: amount of asset cash still remaining to settle the debt
returns.underlyingCashRequiredToSettle: amount of underlying cash still remaining to settle the debt

reduceMaxBorrowCapacity(address,uint80,u.notice: Allows the owner to reduce the max borrow capacity on the vault and force the redemption of strategy tokens to cash to reduce the overall risk of the vault. This method is intended to be used in emergencies to mitigate insolvency risk. The effect of this method will mean that the overall max borrow capacity is reduced, the total used capacity will be unchanged (redeemStrategyTokensToCash does not do any lending to reduce the outstanding fCash), and accounts will be locked out of entering the maturity which was targeted by this method. Other maturities for that vault may still be entered depending on whether or not the vault is above or below the max vault borrow capacity.

params.maturity: the maturity to redeem tokens in, will generally be either the current maturity or the next maturity.
params.maxVaultBorrowCapacity: the new max vault borrow capacity on the primary currency
params.strategyTokensToRedeem: how many tokens we would want to redeem in the maturity
params.vaultData: vault data to pass to the vault

repaySecondaryCurrencyFromVault(address,.notice: Allows a vault to repay a secondary currency that it has borrowed. Will be executed via a callback which will request that the vault repay a specific amount of underlying tokens.

params.account: account that is repaying the secondary currency
params.currencyId: currency id of the secondary currency
params.debtSharesToRepay: amount of debt shares to repay (used to calculate fCashToLend)

returns.returnData: arbitrary return data to pass back to the vault

setMaxBorrowCapacity(address,uint80).notice: Allows the owner to reduce the max borrow capacity on the vault

params.maxVaultBorrowCapacity: the new max vault borrow capacity on the primary currency

setVaultDeleverageStatus(address,bool).notice: Enables or disables deleverage on a vault.

params.disableDeleverage: true if the vault deleverage should be disabled

setVaultPauseStatus(address,bool).notice: Enables or disables a vault. If a vault is disabled, no one can enter the vault but exits are still possible.

params.enable: true if the vault should be enabled immediately

settleVault(address,uint256).notice: Settles a vault and sets the final settlement rates

updateSecondaryBorrowCapacity(address,ui.notice: Whitelists a secondary borrow currency for a vault, vaults can borrow up to the capacity using the `borrowSecondaryCurrencyToVault` and `repaySecondaryCurrencyToVault` methods. Vaults that use a secondary currency must ALWAYS repay the secondary debt during redemption and handle accounting for the secondary currency themselves.
